**Compound interest** accrues interest on both the principal and the previously accumulated interest. The formula is: A = P × (1 + r/n)^(nt), where P is principal, r is annual rate, n is compounding frequency, and t is time in years. The more frequent the compounding, the higher the effective returns — monthly compounding earns more than annual compounding at the same nominal rate.
